{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843110214,"sessionID":"ses_28780c7e5ffetTToawZ272Oixs","part":{"id":"prt_d787f607e001nOyRj0tGWHhEnT","messageID":"msg_d787f51bb00192ZbbTO8yhTgFb","sessionID":"ses_28780c7e5ffetTToawZ272Oixs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bfe33f3d0cc442f1885b0a6b6ddde8ac","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 为 WorkloadManager 构建 HTTP 服务框架，作为 agentcube 核心服务器的网络层基础，提供:\n6: \n7: 1. **RESTful API 基础设施**: 支持 Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session 等资源的 CRUD 操作\n8: 2. **中间件架构**: 提供请求日志、认证、限流、CORS 等可插拔能力\n9: 3. **生命周期管理**: 优雅启动、信号处理、连接清理\n10: 4. **可观测性**: 健康检查、就绪探针、Prometheus 指标端点\n11: 5. **错误处理**: 统一的错误响应格式与日志记录\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: ### In Scope\n16: \n17: | Deliverable | Description |\n18: |-------------|-------------|\n19: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTP 服务器核心实现，包括启动、关闭、配置 |\n20: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | 路由初始化与路由组管理 |\n21: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/base.go` | 基础 Handler 接口定义 |\n22: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | 健康检查与就绪探针实现 |\n23: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` | 请求日志中间件 |\n24: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` | Panic 恢复中间件 |\n25: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` | CORS 中间件（可选） |\n26: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | 请求/响应数据结构定义 |\n27: \n28: ### API Endpoints Framework\n29: \n30: ```\n31: /api/v1/\n32: ├── healthz          — 健康检查 (GET)\n33: ├── readyz           — 就绪探针 (GET)\n34: ├── sandboxes        — Sandbox CRUD (待后续 AR 实现)\n35: ├── sandboxclaims    — SandboxClaim CRUD (待后续 AR 实现)\n36: └── sessions         — Session 管理 (待后续 AR 实现)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### Out of Scope\n40: \n41: - 业务 Handler 实现（Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session）\n42: - WebSocket 路由与连接管理\n43: - 认证授权逻辑\n44: - 具体的限流策略实现\n45: - 数据库/存储层集成\n46: \n47: ## Impact Analysis\n48: \n49: ### Upstream Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Dependency | Impact |\n52: |------------|--------|\n53: | Go 标准库 `net/http` | 核心依赖 |\n54: | 可能的第三方路由库（如 chi, gorilla/mux） | 待设计决策，可选 |\n55: \n56: ### Downstream Consumers\n57: \n58: | Consumer | Usage |\n59: |----------|-------|\n60: | WorkloadManager 业务逻辑 | 通过 Handler 接口注册业务逻辑 |\n61: | 监控系统 | 通过 `/metrics` 端点采集指标 |\n62: | Kubernetes 探针 | 通过 `/healthz`, `/readyz` 检查服务状态 |\n63: | 客户端应用 | 通过 RESTful API 访问服务 |\n64: \n65: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n66: \n67: - **路由路径变更**: API 路径设计影响所有客户端\n68: - **错误格式变更**: 统一错误响应格式影响客户端错误处理逻辑\n69: - **中间件顺序**: 中间件执行顺序可能影响请求处理流程\n70: \n71: ## Alternatives Considered\n72: \n73: ### Alternative 1: 使用标准库 net/http\n74: \n75: **Approach**: 仅使用 `net/http` 标准库，手动实现路由与中间件。\n76: \n77: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n78: |--------|------------|\n79: | Pros | 无外部依赖；完全控制；性能最优 |\n80: | Cons | 路由功能有限；需要手动实现中间件链；缺乏社区生态 |\n81: \n82: **Decision**: 待评估。对于简单场景可行，但路由分组、路径参数等功能需要额外实现。\n83: \n84: ### Alternative 2: 使用 gorilla/mux\n85: \n86: **Approach**: 使用成熟的 `gorilla/mux` 路由库。\n87: \n88: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n89: |--------|------------|\n90: | Pros | 功能完善；社区活跃；中间件支持好 |\n91: | Cons | 外部依赖；性能略逊于 chi |\n92: \n93: **Decision**: 可选方案。\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 3: 使用 chi 路由器\n96: \n97: **Approach**: 使用轻量级 `chi` 路由器。\n98: \n99: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n100: |--------|------------|\n101: | Pros | 零依赖；性能优秀；兼容 net/http；内置中间件 |\n102: | Cons | 社区规模小于 gorilla/mux |\n103: \n104: **Decision**: 推荐。chi 轻量且符合 Go 惯例。\n105: \n106: ### Alternative 4: 使用 Gin/Echo 框架\n107: \n108: **Approach**: 使用完整 Web 框架（Gin 或 Echo）。\n109: \n110: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n111: |--------|------------|\n112: | Pros | 功能全面；性能优秀；生态丰富 |\n113: | Cons | 过度封装；违反 AgentCube 渐进式设计原则 |\n114: \n115: **Decision**: 拒绝。AgentCube 倾向于使用标准库 + 轻量级工具，而非重型框架。\n116: \n117: ## Risks\n118: \n119: | Risk | Mitigation |\n120: |------|------------|\n121: | 路由库选型错误 | 设计阶段充分评估 chi/gorilla/mux/stdlib，保留切换能力 |\n122: | 中间件顺序导致 Bug | 明确中间件执行顺序文档，添加集成测试 |\n123: | 错误响应格式不统一 | 定义 Error 结构体，所有 Handler 使用统一错误返回方法 |\n124: | 性能瓶颈 | 基准测试关键端点，监控 p99 延迟 |\n125: \n126: ## Implementation Notes\n127: \n128: 1. **配置**: 使用环境变量或配置文件指定端口、超时等参数\n129: 2. **日志**: 集成 pkg/logging，记录请求 ID、路径、状态码、延迟\n130: 3. **优雅关闭**: 监听 SIGTERM/SIGINT，等待现有连接完成（最长 30s）\n131: 4. **健康检查**: `/healthz` 总是返回 200，`/readyz` 检查依赖服务状态\n132: 5. **中间件模式**: 使用 Go 标准中间件签名 `func(http.Handler) http.Handler`\n133: \n134: ## References\n135: \n136: - Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n137: - chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n138: - Kubernetes Healthz Pattern: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/configure-liveness-readiness-probes/\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 WorkloadManager 构建 HTTP 服务框架，作为 agentcube 核心服务器的网络层基础，提供:\n\n1. **RESTful API 基础设施**: 支持 Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session 等资源的 CRUD 操作\n2. **中间件架构**: 提供请求日志、认证、限流、CORS 等可插拔能力\n3. **生命周期管理**: 优雅启动、信号处理、连接清理\n4. **可观测性**: 健康检查、就绪探针、Prometheus 指标端点\n5. **错误处理**: 统一的错误响应格式与日志记录\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTP 服务器核心实现，包括启动、关闭、配置 |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | 路由初始化与路由组管理 |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775843110177,"end":1775843110212}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843110216,"sessionID":"ses_28780c7e5ffetTToawZ272Oixs","part":{"id":"prt_d787f64cb001T1fJo3gD9ez4pf","messageID":"msg_d787f51bb00192ZbbTO8yhTgFb","sessionID":"ses_28780c7e5ffetTToawZ272Oixs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3bb8177523194addaf24d89a060d0206","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: 定义 WorkloadManager 的 HTTP 服务框架，包括:\n16: - HTTP 服务器配置与生命周期管理\n17: - 路由设计与中间件架构\n18: - 请求/响应数据结构定义\n19: - 健康检查与指标暴露端点\n20: - 错误处理与日志记录机制\n21: \n22: ## Out of Scope\n23: \n24: - 业务逻辑实现（Sandbox 创建、调度等）\n25: - WebSocket 连接管理\n26: - 认证授权实现\n27: - 具体业务 API 端点实现\n28: \n29: ## Dependencies\n30: \n31: - `net/http` 标准库\n32: - 可能的第三方 HTTP 路由库（待设计确认）\n33: - 日志库（pkg/logging 或第三方）\n34: \n35: ## Deliverables\n36: \n37: | File | Description |\n38: |------|-------------|\n39: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTP 服务器核心实现 |\n40: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | 路由配置与中间件 |\n41: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/` | Handler 接口与基础实现 |\n42: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/` | 中间件实现 |\n43: \n44: ## Acceptance Criteria\n45: \n46: - [ ] HTTP 服务器支持优雅启动和关闭\n47: - [ ] 路由框架可扩展，支持标准 RESTful API\n48: - [ ] 中间件链可配置\n49: - [ ] 健康检查端点可访问\n50: - [ ] 错误响应格式统一\n51: - [ ] 通过 `go vet` 和 `golangci-lint`\n52: \n53: ## References\n54: \n55: - Go net/http 文档: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n定义 WorkloadManager 的 HTTP 服务框架，包括:\n- HTTP 服务器配置与生命周期管理\n- 路由设计与中间件架构\n- 请求/响应数据结构定义\n- 健康检查与指标暴露端点\n- 错误处理与日志记录机制","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/spec.md","time":{"start":1775843110180,"end":1775843110215}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843110219,"sessionID":"ses_28780c7e5ffetTToawZ272Oixs","part":{"id":"prt_d787f68dd001zCzeUmy8cJQwYy","messageID":"msg_d787f51bb00192ZbbTO8yhTgFb","sessionID":"ses_28780c7e5ffetTToawZ272Oixs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-38869c0cfc624e6cb4d9c3b62ef9e796","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 定义 WorkloadManager 的 HTTP 服务框架，提供 RESTful API 基础设施、中间件架构、生命周期管理。\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: ### Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: cmd/workload-manager/\n21:     └── main.go                    — 入口，调用 pkg/workloadmanager\n22: pkg/workloadmanager/\n23:     ├── server.go                  — HTTPServer 核心实现\n24:     ├── router.go                  — 路由配置与路由组\n25:     ├── config.go                  — 配置结构体\n26:     ├── types.go                   — 公共类型定义\n27:     ├── doc.go                     — 包文档\n28:     ├── handlers/\n29:     │   ├── handler.go             — Handler 接口\n30:     │   └── health.go              — 健康检查实现\n31:     └── middleware/\n32:         ├── logging.go             — 请求日志中间件\n33:         ├── recovery.go            — Panic 恢复中间件\n34:         └── cors.go                — CORS 中间件\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Kubernetes Client Integration\n38: \n39: WorkloadManager 使用 `client-go` 与 Kubernetes API 交互:\n40: \n41: | Client | API Group | Resource | Purpose |\n42: |--------|-----------|----------|---------|\n43: | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | `agentruntimes` | 管理 AgentRuntime CR |\n44: | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | `codeinterpreters` | 管理 CodeInterpreter CR |\n45: \n46: Client construction pattern:\n47: \n48: ```go\n49: import (\n50:     versioned \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n51:     \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n52: )\n53: \n54: func NewKubernetesClient(config *rest.Config) (versioned.Interface, error) {\n55:     return versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n56: }\n57: ```\n58: \n59: Typed client interfaces:\n60: \n61: ```go\n62: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n63:     RESTClient() rest.Interface\n64:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n65:     CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n66: }\n67: \n68: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n69:     Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n70:     Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n71:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n72:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n73:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n74:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n75:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n76:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n77: }\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Dependencies\n81: \n82: | Package | Purpose |\n83: |---------|---------|\n84: | `net/http` | 标准库 HTTP 服务器 |\n85: | `context` | 请求上下文 |\n86: | `sync` | 并发控制（优雅关闭） |\n87: | `os/signal` | 信号处理 |\n88: | `time` | 超时配置 |\n89: | `encoding/json` | JSON 序列化 |\n90: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP 路由器 |\n91: | `k8s.io/client-go/rest` | Kubernetes REST 配置 |\n92: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | 生成的 typed client |\n93: \n94: ### Router Library Selection\n95: \n96: **决策**: 使用 `go-chi/chi` v5\n97: \n98: | Aspect | Rationale |\n99: |--------|-----------|\n100: | 零外部依赖 | 仅依赖 Go 标准库 |\n101: | 兼容 net/http | 可使用所有标准库中间件 |\n102: | 路由分组 | 支持路由组与中间件作用域 |\n103: | 性能 | 足够优秀（参考 benchmark） |\n104: \n105: ## Data Structures\n106: \n107: ### server.go\n108: \n109: ```go\n110: type HTTPServer struct {\n111:     server   *http.Server\n112:     router   chi.Router\n113:     config   Config\n114:     handlers map[string]Handler\n115:     logger   Logger\n116:     stopCh   chan struct{}\n117: }\n118: \n119: func NewHTTPServer(cfg Config, logger Logger) *HTTPServer {\n120:     return &HTTPServer{\n121:         server:   &http.Server{Addr: cfg.Addr},\n122:         router:   chi.NewRouter(),\n123:         config:   cfg,\n124:         handlers: make(map[string]Handler),\n125:         logger:   logger,\n126:         stopCh:   make(chan struct{}),\n127:     }\n128: }\n129: \n130: func (s *HTTPServer) Start() <-chan error {\n131:     errCh := make(chan error, 1)\n132:     s.server.ReadTimeout = s.config.ReadTimeout\n133:     s.server.WriteTimeout = s.config.WriteTimeout\n134:     s.server.IdleTimeout = s.config.IdleTimeout\n135:     go func() {\n136:         if err := s.server.ListenAndServe(); err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n137:             errCh <- err\n138:         }\n139:     }()\n140:     return errCh\n141: }\n142: \n143: func (s *HTTPServer) Stop(ctx context.Context) error {\n144:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, s.config.ShutdownTimeout)\n145:     defer cancel()\n146:     err := s.server.Shutdown(ctx)\n147:     close(s.stopCh)\n148:     return err\n149: }\n150: \n151: func (s *HTTPServer) GracefulShutdown() {\n152:     sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n153:     signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n154:     go func() {\n155:         <-sigCh\n156:         ctx := context.Background()\n157:         s.Stop(ctx)\n158:     }()\n159: }\n160: \n161: func (s *HTTPServer) RegisterHandler(name string, h Handler) {\n162:     s.handlers[name] = h\n163:     h.Register(s.router)\n164: }\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ### config.go\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: type Config struct {\n171:     Addr              string        // 监听地址，如 \":8080\"\n172:     ReadTimeout       time.Duration // 读超时\n173:     WriteTimeout      time.Duration // 写超时\n174:     IdleTimeout       time.Duration // 空闲连接超时\n175:     ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration // 优雅关闭超时\n176:     EnableHealthz     bool          // 是否启用健康检查\n177:     EnableReadyz      bool          // 是否启用就绪探针\n178: }\n179: \n180: func DefaultConfig() Config {\n181:     return Config{\n182:         Addr:            \":8080\",\n183:         ReadTimeout:     15 * time.Second,\n184:         WriteTimeout:    15 * time.Second,\n185:         IdleTimeout:     60 * time.Second,\n186:         ShutdownTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n187:         EnableHealthz:   true,\n188:         EnableReadyz:    true,\n189:     }\n190: }\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### router.go\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: type Router struct {\n197:     chi.Router\n198: }\n199: \n200: func NewRouter() *Router {\n201:     r := chi.NewRouter()\n202:     return &Router{Router: r}\n203: }\n204: \n205: func (r *Router) RegisterHandlers(handlers ...Handler) {\n206:     for _, h := range handlers {\n207:         h.Register(r.Router)\n208:     }\n209: }\n210: ```\n211: \n212: ### handlers/handler.go\n213: \n214: ```go\n215: type Handler interface {\n216:     Register(r chi.Router)\n217: }\n218: \n219: type HandlerFunc func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n220: \n221: func (hf HandlerFunc) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n222:     if err := hf(w, r); err != nil {\n223:         HandleError(w, r, err)\n224:     }\n225: }\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ### handlers/health.go\n229: \n230: ```go\n231: type HealthChecker interface {\n232:     IsHealthy() bool\n233:     IsReady() bool\n234: }\n235: \n236: type HealthHandler struct {\n237:     checker HealthChecker\n238: }\n239: \n240: func NewHealthHandler(checker HealthChecker) *HealthHandler {\n241:     return &HealthHandler{checker: checker}\n242: }\n243: \n244: func (h *HealthHandler) Register(r chi.Router) {\n245:     r.Get(\"/healthz\", h.healthz)\n246:     r.Get(\"/readyz\", h.readyz)\n247: }\n248: \n249: func (h *HealthHandler) healthz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n250:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n251:     w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n252:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n253: }\n254: \n255: func (h *HealthHandler) readyz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n256:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n257:     if h.checker == nil || !h.checker.IsReady() {\n258:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n259:         json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"not ready\"})\n260:         return\n261:     }\n262:     w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n263:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ready\"})\n264: }\n265: ```\n266: \n267: ### middleware/logging.go\n268: \n269: ```go\n270: type LoggingMiddleware struct {\n271:     logger Logger\n272: }\n273: \n274: func NewLoggingMiddleware(logger Logger) *LoggingMiddleware {\n275:     return &LoggingMiddleware{logger: logger}\n276: }\n277: \n278: type responseWriterWrapper struct {\n279:     http.ResponseWriter\n280:     status int\n281: }\n282: \n283: func (w *responseWriterWrapper) WriteHeader(code int) {\n284:     w.status = code\n285:     w.ResponseWriter.WriteHeader(code)\n286: }\n287: \n288: func (m *LoggingMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n289:     return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n290:         start := time.Now()\n291:         \n292:         ww := &responseWriterWrapper{ResponseWriter: w}\n293:         next.ServeHTTP(ww, r)\n294:         \n295:         m.logger.Info(\"request\",\n296:             \"method\", r.Method,\n297:             \"path\", r.URL.Path,\n298:             \"status\", ww.status,\n299:             \"duration\", time.Since(start),\n300:         )\n301:     })\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ### middleware/recovery.go\n306: \n307: ```go\n308: type RecoveryMiddleware struct {\n309:     logger Logger\n310: }\n311: \n312: func NewRecoveryMiddleware(logger Logger) *RecoveryMiddleware {\n313:     return &RecoveryMiddleware{logger: logger}\n314: }\n315: \n316: func (m *RecoveryMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n317:     return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n318:         defer func() {\n319:             if err := recover(); err != nil {\n320:                 m.logger.Error(\"panic recovered\", \"error\", err, \"path\", r.URL.Path)\n321:                 http.Error(w, \"Internal Server Error\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n322:             }\n323:         }()\n324:         next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n325:     })\n326: }\n327: ```\n328: \n329: ### middleware/cors.go\n330: \n331: ```go\n332: type CORSConfig struct {\n333:     AllowedOrigins   []string\n334:     AllowedMethods   []string\n335:     AllowedHeaders   []string\n336:     AllowCredentials bool\n337: }\n338: \n339: type CORSMiddleware struct {\n340:     config CORSConfig\n341: }\n342: \n343: func NewCORSMiddleware(config CORSConfig) *CORSMiddleware {\n344:     return &CORSMiddleware{config: config}\n345: }\n346: \n347: func (m *CORSMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n348:     return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n349:         origin := r.Header.Get(\"Origin\")\n350:         if origin != \"\" && m.isAllowedOrigin(origin) {\n351:             w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Origin\", origin)\n352:             w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Methods\", strings.Join(m.config.AllowedMethods, \",\"))\n353:             w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Headers\", strings.Join(m.config.AllowedHeaders, \",\"))\n354:             if m.config.AllowCredentials {\n355:                 w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Credentials\", \"true\")\n356:             }\n357:         }\n358:         \n359:         if r.Method == \"OPTIONS\" {\n360:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n361:             return\n362:         }\n363:         \n364:         next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n365:     })\n366: }\n367: \n368: func (m *CORSMiddleware) isAllowedOrigin(origin string) bool {\n369:     for _, o := range m.config.AllowedOrigins {\n370:         if o == \"*\" || o == origin {\n371:             return true\n372:         }\n373:     }\n374:     return false\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### types.go\n379: \n380: ```go\n381: type Logger interface {\n382:     Info(msg string, args ...any)\n383:     Error(msg string, args ...any)\n384: }\n385: \n386: type ErrorResponse struct {\n387:     Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n388:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n389:     Details any    `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n390: }\n391: \n392: type SuccessResponse struct {\n393:     Data any `json:\"data\"`\n394: }\n395: \n396: type ValidationError struct {\n397:     Field   string\n398:     Reason  string\n399: }\n400: \n401: func (e *ValidationError) Error() string {\n402:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"validation error: %s - %s\", e.Field, e.Reason)\n403: }\n404: \n405: type NotFoundError struct {\n406:     Resource string\n407:     Name     string\n408: }\n409: \n410: func (e *NotFoundError) Error() string {\n411:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"not found: %s/%s\", e.Resource, e.Name)\n412: }\n413: \n414: type InternalError struct {\n415:     Err error\n416: }\n417: \n418: func (e *InternalError) Error() string {\n419:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"internal error: %v\", e.Err)\n420: }\n421: \n422: type ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n423:     Dependency string\n424: }\n425: \n426: func (e *ServiceUnavailableError) Error() string {\n427:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"service unavailable: %s\", e.Dependency)\n428: }\n429: \n430: func HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, err error) {\n431:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n432:     \n433:     var resp ErrorResponse\n434:     var status int\n435:     \n436:     switch e := err.(type) {\n437:     case *ValidationError:\n438:         status = http.StatusBadRequest\n439:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n440:             Code:    \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n441:             Message: \"Invalid request parameter\",\n442:             Details: map[string]string{\"field\": e.Field, \"reason\": e.Reason},\n443:         }\n444:     case *NotFoundError:\n445:         status = http.StatusNotFound\n446:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n447:             Code:    \"NOT_FOUND\",\n448:             Message: e.Error(),\n449:         }\n450:     case *ServiceUnavailableError:\n451:         status = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n452:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n453:             Code:    \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\",\n454:             Message: e.Error(),\n455:         }\n456:     case *InternalError:\n457:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n458:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n459:             Code:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n460:             Message: \"Unexpected server error\",\n461:         }\n462:     default:\n463:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n464:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n465:             Code:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n466:             Message: \"Unexpected server error\",\n467:         }\n468:     }\n469:     \n470:     w.WriteHeader(status)\n471:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ## API Endpoints\n476: \n477: ### Health Endpoints\n478: \n479: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Response |\n480: |----------|--------|---------|----------|\n481: | `/healthz` | GET | Kubernetes liveness probe | `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` (HTTP 200) |\n482: | `/readyz` | GET | Kubernetes readiness probe | `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` (HTTP 200) or `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` (HTTP 503) |\n483: \n484: ### Health Endpoint Acceptance Criteria\n485: \n486: | Scenario | Request | Expected Response |\n487: |----------|---------|-------------------|\n488: | healthz always OK | GET /healthz | HTTP 200, `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n489: | readyz with checker ready | GET /readyz (checker.IsReady()=true) | HTTP 200, `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` |\n490: | readyz with checker not ready | GET /readyz (checker.IsReady()=false) | HTTP 503, `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n491: | readyz without checker | GET /readyz (checker=nil) | HTTP 503, `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n492: \n493: ### API Group\n494: \n495: | Prefix | Purpose |\n496: |--------|---------|\n497: | `/api/v1` | 业务 API 路由组（待后续 AR 实现） |\n498: \n499: ### Middleware Chain\n500: \n501: ```\n502: Recovery → Logging → CORS (optional) → Business Handler\n503: ```\n504: \n505: ### Middleware Chain Acceptance Criteria\n506: \n507: | Scenario | Input | Expected Behavior |\n508: |----------|-------|-------------------|\n509: | Recovery catches panic | Handler panics | Recovery middleware catches panic before Logging logs |\n510: | Logging captures duration | Normal request | Logging captures full request duration including handler execution |\n511: | CORS optional | CORS not configured | CORS middleware NOT applied to chain |\n512: \n513: ## Error Handling\n514: \n515: ### Error Type Mapping\n516: \n517: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code | Description |\n518: |------------|-------------|------------|-------------|\n519: | ValidationError | 400 | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | Invalid request parameter |\n520: | NotFoundError | 404 | `NOT_FOUND` | Resource not found |\n521: | InternalError | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | Unexpected server error |\n522: | ServiceUnavailableError | 503 | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | Dependency unavailable |\n523: \n524: ### Error Response Format\n525: \n526: 统一错误响应格式:\n527: ```json\n528: {\n529:   \"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n530:   \"message\": \"Invalid request parameter\",\n531:   \"details\": {\"field\": \"name\", \"reason\": \"required\"}\n532: }\n533: ```\n534: \n535: ### Error Handling Acceptance Criteria\n536: \n537: | Scenario | Error Type | Expected Response |\n538: |----------|------------|-------------------|\n539: | Validation error | ValidationError | HTTP 400, `{\"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", ...}` |\n540: | Not found error | NotFoundError | HTTP 404, `{\"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\", ...}` |\n541: | Internal error | InternalError | HTTP 500, `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", ...}` |\n542: | Service unavailable | ServiceUnavailableError | HTTP 503, `{\"code\": \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\", ...}` |\n543: | Unknown error | any other | HTTP 500, `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", ...}` |\n544: \n545: ### Response Headers\n546: \n547: All error responses MUST include:\n548: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n549: \n550: ## Testing Strategy\n551: \n552: ### Unit Tests\n553: \n554: | Test File | Test Category | Coverage Target |\n555: |-----------|---------------|-----------------|\n556: | `server_test.go` | HTTPServer 启动/关闭 | 测试优雅关闭逻辑、超时处理 |\n557: | `router_test.go` | Router 初始化/注册 | 测试 NewRouter、RegisterHandlers |\n558: | `types_test.go` | HandleError/响应类型 | 测试正确 JSON 格式和状态码 |\n559: | `handlers/health_test.go` | healthz/readyz | 测试 HTTP 200/503 响应 |\n560: | `middleware/logging_test.go` | 请求日志 | 测试 method/path/status 捕获 |\n561: | `middleware/recovery_test.go` | Panic 恢复 | 测试 HTTP 500 响应 |\n562: | `middleware/cors_test.go` | CORS 头 | 测试 Access-Control 头、OPTIONS 处理 |\n563: \n564: ### Unit Test Acceptance Criteria\n565: \n566: | Test | Expected Behavior |\n567: |------|-------------------|\n568: | NewHTTPServer | Returns server with router initialized using chi.NewRouter() |\n569: | HTTPServer.Start | Returns error channel, starts ListenAndServe |\n570: | HTTPServer.Stop | Calls Shutdown with context timeout, closes stopCh |\n571: | GracefulShutdown | Sets up SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers |\n572: | RegisterHandlers | Each handler's Register method called |\n573: | HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP | Calls handler, handles errors via HandleError |\n574: | healthz endpoint | HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n575: | readyz endpoint (ready) | HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` |\n576: | readyz endpoint (not ready) | HTTP 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n577: | LoggingMiddleware.Wrap | Captures method, path, status, duration |\n578: | responseWriterWrapper.WriteHeader | Sets status code, calls embedded WriteHeader |\n579: | RecoveryMiddleware.Wrap | Recovers panic, returns HTTP 500 |\n580: | CORSMiddleware.Wrap | Adds Access-Control-Allow-Origin header |\n581: | CORS OPTIONS request | HTTP 200 with preflight headers |\n582: \n583: ### Integration Tests\n584: \n585: | Test | Description |\n586: |------|-------------|\n587: | End-to-end health check | 启动真实 HTTP 服务器，GET /healthz 返回 HTTP 200 |\n588: | End-to-end readiness check | 启动服务器，GET /readyz 返回匹配 HealthChecker 状态 |\n589: | Middleware chain verification | 验证中间件按正确顺序执行 |\n590: | Panic recovery in integration | 服务器不崩溃，返回 HTTP 500 |\n591: \n592: ### Integration Test Acceptance Criteria\n593: \n594: | Test | Expected Behavior |\n595: |------|-------------------|\n596: | E2E healthz | GET /healthz on running server → HTTP 200 with correct JSON |\n597: | E2E readyz | GET /readyz matches HealthChecker.IsReady() state |\n598: | Middleware order | Recovery → Logging → Handler executes correctly |\n599: | Panic recovery | Server does NOT crash, response is HTTP 500 |\n600: \n601: ### Test Coverage Requirements\n602: \n603: | Requirement | Threshold |\n604: |-------------|-----------|\n605: | Overall coverage | > 80% |\n606: | Package coverage | > 80% per package |\n607: \n608: ### Test File Structure\n609: \n610: ```\n611: pkg/workloadmanager/\n612:   server_test.go\n613:   router_test.go\n614:   types_test.go\n615:   handlers/health_test.go\n616:   middleware/logging_test.go\n617:   middleware/recovery_test.go\n618:   middleware/cors_test.go\n619:   integration_test.go\n620: ```\n621: \n622: ### Code Quality Requirements\n623: \n624: | Check | Command | Expected |\n625: |-------|---------|----------|\n626: | go vet | `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Zero issues |\n627: | golangci-lint | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Zero issues |\n628: | go build | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Build succeeds |\n629: | go test | `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Coverage > 80% |\n630: \n631: ## File Structure\n632: \n633: ```\n634: pkg/workloadmanager/\n635:   server.go              — HTTPServer 实现\n636:   router.go              — Router 封装\n637:   config.go              — Config 结构体 + DefaultConfig\n638:   types.go               — ErrorResponse, SuccessResponse, HandleError, Logger, error types\n639:   doc.go                 — Package-level godoc\n640:   handlers/\n641:     handler.go           — Handler 接口 + HandlerFunc\n642:     health.go            — HealthHandler + HealthChecker\n643:   middleware/\n644:     logging.go           — LoggingMiddleware + responseWriterWrapper\n645:     recovery.go          — RecoveryMiddleware\n646:     cors.go              — CORSMiddleware + CORSConfig\n647: ```\n648: \n649: ## Validation Checklist\n650: \n651: - [ ] HTTPServer struct contains: server, router, config, handlers, logger, stopCh\n652: - [ ] Config struct contains: Addr, ReadTimeout, WriteTimeout, IdleTimeout, ShutdownTimeout, EnableHealthz, EnableReadyz\n653: - [ ] DefaultConfig returns: Addr \":8080\", ReadTimeout 15s, WriteTimeout 15s, IdleTimeout 60s, ShutdownTimeout 30s\n654: - [ ] NewHTTPServer initializes router with chi.NewRouter()\n655: - [ ] HTTPServer.Start returns error channel, starts ListenAndServe\n656: - [ ] HTTPServer.Stop calls Shutdown with context timeout\n657: - [ ] HTTPServer.GracefulShutdown handles SIGTERM/SIGINT\n658: - [ ] Router struct embeds chi.Router\n659: - [ ] RegisterHandlers calls each handler's Register method\n660: - [ ] Handler interface defines Register(r chi.Router)\n661: - [ ] HandlerFunc type: func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n662: - [ ] HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP calls HandleError on error\n663: - [ ] RegisterHandler stores handler in map and registers on router\n664: - [ ] HealthChecker interface defines IsHealthy() and IsReady()\n665: - [ ] healthz endpoint returns HTTP 200 with {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n666: - [ ] readyz endpoint returns HTTP 200/503 based on checker state\n667: - [ ] LoggingMiddleware.Wrap captures method, path, status, duration\n668: - [ ] responseWriterWrapper captures status code\n669: - [ ] RecoveryMiddleware.Wrap catches panic, returns HTTP 500\n670: - [ ] CORSMiddleware.Wrap adds Access-Control-Allow-Origin header\n671: - [ ] CORS OPTIONS request returns HTTP 200 with preflight headers\n672: - [ ] ErrorResponse struct: Code, Message, Details\n673: - [ ] SuccessResponse struct: Data\n674: - [ ] HandleError maps error types to HTTP status codes\n675: - [ ] HandleError sets Content-Type: application/json\n676: - [ ] Middleware chain: Recovery → Logging → CORS → Handler\n677: - [ ] Pass `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n678: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n679: - [ ] Pass `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` with >80% coverage\n680: - [ ] All exported types have godoc comments\n681: \n682: ## Open Questions\n683: \n684: - 是否需要 WebSocket 支持？（暂不在范围内，待后续 AR）\n685: - 是否需要限流中间件？（暂不在范围内，待后续 AR）\n686: - 日志库选型：pkg/logging 还是第三方（如 zap、logrus）？\n687: - 指标端点 `/metrics` 是否在本 AR 范围内？（建议预留路由，实现待后续 AR）\n688: \n689: ## References\n690: \n691: - chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n692: - Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n693: - Kubernetes API conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n694: - client-go: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n695: - AgentRuntime types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n696: - CodeInterpreter types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n697: - Shared types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n698: - AR-003 Design: `changes/AR-003/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 698 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n定义 WorkloadManager 的 HTTP 服务框架，提供 RESTful API 基础设施、中间件架构、生命周期管理。\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\ncmd/workload-manager/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md","time":{"start":1775843110183,"end":1775843110216}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843110223,"sessionID":"ses_28780c7e5ffetTToawZ272Oixs","part":{"id":"prt_d787f6cc3001O9afDh7zbBQv57","messageID":"msg_d787f51bb00192ZbbTO8yhTgFb","sessionID":"ses_28780c7e5ffetTToawZ272Oixs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-858850beef334baaacd61a0c9c31c213","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Project Setup\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Create directory structure `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n20:   - Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n21:   - Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`\n22:   - Verify: `ls pkg/workloadmanager/ handlers/ middleware/`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2** Add dependency `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` to `go.mod`\n25:   - Verify: `grep -q \"go-chi/chi/v5\" go.mod`\n26: \n27: ### Phase 2: Core Type Definitions\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go`\n30:   - Add package-level godoc documentation\n31:   - Verify: `test -f pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go`\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T2.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Logger interface\n34:   - Define `Logger` interface with `Info(msg string, args ...any)` and `Error(msg string, args ...any)`\n35:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type Logger interface\" pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n36: \n37: - [ ] **T2.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Response types\n38:   - Define `ErrorResponse` struct with fields: `Code`, `Message`, `Details`\n39:   - Define `SuccessResponse` struct with field: `Data`\n40:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type ErrorResponse struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n41: \n42: - [ ] **T2.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Error types\n43:   - Define `ValidationError` struct with `Field`, `Reason` fields and `Error()` method\n44:   - Define `NotFoundError` struct with `Resource`, `Name` fields and `Error()` method\n45:   - Define `InternalError` struct with `Err` field and `Error()` method\n46:   - Define `ServiceUnavailableError` struct with `Dependency` field and `Error()` method\n47:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type ValidationError struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T2.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - HandleError function\n50:   - Define `HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, err error)` function\n51:   - Map error types to HTTP status codes and JSON responses\n52:   - Set `Content-Type: application/json` header\n53:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func HandleError\" pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T2.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/config.go` - Config struct\n56:   - Define `Config` struct with fields: `Addr`, `ReadTimeout`, `WriteTimeout`, `IdleTimeout`, `ShutdownTimeout`, `EnableHealthz`, `EnableReadyz`\n57:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type Config struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/config.go`\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T2.7** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/config.go` - DefaultConfig\n60:   - Define `DefaultConfig()` returning: Addr \":8080\", ReadTimeout 15s, WriteTimeout 15s, IdleTimeout 60s, ShutdownTimeout 30s\n61:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func DefaultConfig\" pkg/workloadmanager/config.go`\n62: \n63: ### Phase 3: Router Implementation\n64: \n65: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` - Router struct\n66:   - Import `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5`\n67:   - Define `Router` struct embedding `chi.Router`\n68:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type Router struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/router.go`\n69: \n70: - [ ] **T3.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` - NewRouter constructor\n71:   - Implement `NewRouter()` returning `*Router` with `chi.NewRouter()`\n72:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func NewRouter\" pkg/workloadmanager/router.go`\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T3.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` - RegisterHandlers method\n75:   - Implement `RegisterHandlers(handlers ...Handler)` calling each handler's `Register` method\n76:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*RegisterHandlers\" pkg/workloadmanager/router.go`\n77: \n78: ### Phase 4: Handler Interface & Health Handler\n79: \n80: - [ ] **T4.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go` - Handler interface\n81:   - Define `Handler` interface with `Register(r chi.Router)` method\n82:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type Handler interface\" pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go`\n83: \n84: - [ ] **T4.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go` - HandlerFunc type\n85:   - Define `HandlerFunc` type: `func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error`\n86:   - Implement `ServeHTTP` that calls handler and handles errors via `HandleError`\n87:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type HandlerFunc\" pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go`\n88: \n89: - [ ] **T4.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` - HealthChecker interface\n90:   - Define `HealthChecker` interface with `IsHealthy()` and `IsReady()` methods\n91:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type HealthChecker interface\" pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T4.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` - HealthHandler struct\n94:   - Define `HealthHandler` struct with `checker HealthChecker` field\n95:   - Implement `NewHealthHandler(checker HealthChecker) *HealthHandler`\n96:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type HealthHandler struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T4.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` - Register method\n99:   - Implement `Register(r chi.Router)` registering `/healthz` and `/readyz` routes\n100:   - Verify: `grep -q \"r.Get.*healthz\" pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T4.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` - healthz handler\n103:   - Implement `healthz` returning HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n104:   - Set `Content-Type: application/json`\n105:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*healthz\" pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n106: \n107: - [ ] **T4.7** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` - readyz handler\n108:   - Implement `readyz` returning HTTP 200/503 based on `checker.IsReady()` state\n109:   - Return HTTP 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` when checker nil or not ready\n110:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*readyz\" pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n111: \n112: ### Phase 5: Middleware Implementation\n113: \n114: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` - responseWriterWrapper\n115:   - Define `responseWriterWrapper` struct wrapping `http.ResponseWriter` with `status int` field\n116:   - Implement `WriteHeader(code int)` capturing status code\n117:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type responseWriterWrapper struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go`\n118: \n119: - [ ] **T5.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` - LoggingMiddleware struct\n120:   - Define `LoggingMiddleware` struct with `logger Logger` field\n121:   - Implement `NewLoggingMiddleware(logger Logger) *LoggingMiddleware`\n122:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type LoggingMiddleware struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go`\n123: \n124: - [ ] **T5.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` - Wrap method\n125:   - Implement `Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler` capturing method, path, status, duration\n126:   - Log request after handler completes\n127:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*Wrap\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go`\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T5.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` - RecoveryMiddleware struct\n130:   - Define `RecoveryMiddleware` struct with `logger Logger` field\n131:   - Implement `NewRecoveryMiddleware(logger Logger) *RecoveryMiddleware`\n132:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type RecoveryMiddleware struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go`\n133: \n134: - [ ] **T5.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` - Wrap method\n135:   - Implement `Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler` with defer recover\n136:   - Log panic and return HTTP 500 on panic\n137:   - Verify: `grep -q \"recover()\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go`\n138: \n139: - [ ] **T5.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` - CORSConfig struct\n140:   - Define `CORSConfig` struct with fields: `AllowedOrigins`, `AllowedMethods`, `AllowedHeaders`, `AllowCredentials`\n141:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type CORSConfig struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go`\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T5.7** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` - CORSMiddleware struct\n144:   - Define `CORSMiddleware` struct with `config CORSConfig` field\n145:   - Implement `NewCORSMiddleware(config CORSConfig) *CORSMiddleware`\n146:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type CORSMiddleware struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go`\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T5.8** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` - Wrap method\n149:   - Implement `Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler` adding Access-Control headers\n150:   - Handle OPTIONS preflight returning HTTP 200\n151:   - Verify: `grep -q \"Access-Control-Allow-Origin\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go`\n152: \n153: - [ ] **T5.9** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` - isAllowedOrigin helper\n154:   - Implement `isAllowedOrigin(origin string) bool` checking against AllowedOrigins (including \"*\" wildcard)\n155:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*isAllowedOrigin\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go`\n156: \n157: ### Phase 6: Server Implementation\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - HTTPServer struct\n160:   - Define `HTTPServer` struct with fields: `server *http.Server`, `router chi.Router`, `config Config`, `handlers map[string]Handler`, `logger Logger`, `stopCh chan struct{}`\n161:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type HTTPServer struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n162: \n163: - [ ] **T6.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - NewHTTPServer constructor\n164:   - Implement `NewHTTPServer(cfg Config, logger Logger) *HTTPServer`\n165:   - Initialize router with `chi.NewRouter()`\n166:   - Initialize handlers map and stopCh channel\n167:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func NewHTTPServer\" pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n168: \n169: - [ ] **T6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - RegisterHandler method\n170:   - Implement `RegisterHandler(name string, h Handler)` storing in map and calling `h.Register(router)`\n171:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*RegisterHandler\" pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T6.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Start method\n174:   - Implement `Start() <-chan error` returning error channel\n175:   - Configure `http.Server` timeouts: ReadTimeout, WriteTimeout, IdleTimeout\n176:   - Start `ListenAndServe` goroutine, send errors to channel\n177:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*Start\" pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n178: \n179: - [ ] **T6.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Stop method\n180:   - Implement `Stop(ctx context.Context) error` with ShutdownTimeout context\n181:   - Call `server.Shutdown(ctx)` and close `stopCh`\n182:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*Stop\" pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n183: \n184: - [ ] **T6.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - GracefulShutdown method\n185:   - Implement `GracefulShutdown()` setting up SIGTERM/SIGINT signal handlers\n186:   - Call `Stop(context.Background())` on signal\n187:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*GracefulShutdown\" pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n188: \n189: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T7.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go` - HandleError tests\n192:   - Test `HandleError` with `ValidationError` returns HTTP 400, code `VALIDATION_ERROR`\n193:   - Test `HandleError` with `NotFoundError` returns HTTP 404, code `NOT_FOUND`\n194:   - Test `HandleError` with `InternalError` returns HTTP 500, code `INTERNAL_ERROR`\n195:   - Test `HandleError` with `ServiceUnavailableError` returns HTTP 503, code `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE`\n196:   - Test `HandleError` with unknown error returns HTTP 500, code `INTERNAL_ERROR`\n197:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestHandleError -v`\n198: \n199: - [ ] **T7.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go` - Error type tests\n200:   - Test `ValidationError.Error()` returns correct format\n201:   - Test `NotFoundError.Error()` returns correct format\n202:   - Test `InternalError.Error()` returns correct format\n203:   - Test `ServiceUnavailableError.Error()` returns correct format\n204:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestErrorTypes -v`\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T7.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` - NewHTTPServer test\n207:   - Test `NewHTTPServer` returns server with router initialized using `chi.NewRouter()`\n208:   - Test server has correct config and nil handlers map initialized\n209:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestNewHTTPServer -v`\n210: \n211: - [ ] **T7.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` - RegisterHandler test\n212:   - Test `RegisterHandler` stores handler in map\n213:   - Test handler's `Register` method is called\n214:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestRegisterHandler -v`\n215: \n216: - [ ] **T7.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/router_test.go` - NewRouter test\n217:   - Test `NewRouter()` returns valid router with chi.Router embedded\n218:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestNewRouter -v`\n219: \n220: - [ ] **T7.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/router_test.go` - RegisterHandlers test\n221:   - Test `RegisterHandlers` calls each handler's `Register` method\n222:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestRegisterHandlers -v`\n223: \n224: - [ ] **T7.7** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go` - healthz test\n225:   - Test GET `/healthz` returns HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n226:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestHealthz -v`\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T7.8** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go` - readyz with checker ready\n229:   - Test GET `/readyz` with `IsReady()=true` returns HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ready\"}`\n230:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestReadyzReady -v`\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T7.9** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go` - readyz without checker\n233:   - Test GET `/readyz` with nil checker returns HTTP 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}`\n234:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestReadyzNoChecker -v`\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T7.10** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go` - readyz checker not ready\n237:   - Test GET `/readyz` with `IsReady()=false` returns HTTP 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}`\n238:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestReadyzNotReady -v`\n239: \n240: - [ ] **T7.11** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler_test.go` - HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP test\n241:   - Test `HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP` calls handler function\n242:   - Test `HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP` calls `HandleError` on error\n243:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestHandlerFunc -v`\n244: \n245: - [ ] **T7.12** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go` - responseWriterWrapper test\n246:   - Test `responseWriterWrapper.WriteHeader` captures status code\n247:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/... -run TestResponseWriterWrapper -v`\n248: \n249: - [ ] **T7.13** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go` - LoggingMiddleware.Wrap test\n250:   - Test middleware captures method, path, status, duration\n251:   - Ve