9.5** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n323:   - Fix any linting issues\n324:   - Verify: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` (zero issues)\n325: \n326: - [ ] **T9.6** Verify `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` succeeds\n327:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n328: \n329: - [ ] **T9.7** Verify test coverage > 80%\n330:   - Run: `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n331:   - Verify coverage threshold\n332: \n333: - [ ] **T9.8** Verify middleware chain order: Recovery → Logging → CORS → Handler\n334:   - Recovery catches panic before Logging logs\n335:   - Logging captures full request duration\n336:   - Verify in design or code comments\n337: \n338: - [ ] **T9.9** Verify graceful shutdown behavior\n339:   - Send SIGTERM signal to running server\n340:   - Verify server stops accepting new connections\n341:   - Verify existing connections complete within timeout\n342:   - Verify: manual test or integration test\n343: \n344: - [ ] **T9.10** Verify health endpoints work with Kubernetes probes\n345:   - Test `curl http://localhost:8080/healthz` returns HTTP 200\n346:   - Test `curl http://localhost:8080/readyz` returns correct status\n347: \n348: ### Phase 10: Documentation\n349: \n350: - [ ] **T10.1** Add godoc comments to `HTTPServer` struct and all methods\n351:   - Verify: `grep -c \"// HTTPServer\" pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n352: \n353: - [ ] **T10.2** Add godoc comments to `Config` struct and `DefaultConfig`\n354:   - Verify: `grep -c \"// Config\" pkg/workloadmanager/config.go`\n355: \n356: - [ ] **T10.3** Add godoc comments to all middleware types\n357:   - Verify: `grep -c \"// LoggingMiddleware\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go`\n358: \n359: - [ ] **T10.4** Add godoc comments to all error types\n360:   - Verify: `grep -c \"// ValidationError\" pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n361: \n362: - [ ] **T10.5** Add package-level documentation in `pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go`\n363:   - Describe HTTP server fram